<TEXT>
an 11yearold american pilot who hopes to 
become the youngest person to fly around the world landed his small 
cessna 210 centurion sunday after flying across the icy north 
atlantic 
it was like flying over a big lake said tony aliengena after 
the nearly sixhour flight over the often stormswept 1100 miles of 
ocean probably the longest most treacherous leg of the flight 
tony landed his singleengine turboprop cessna in oslo late 
sunday about 10 minutes after an escort plane carrying his mother 
sister and soviet and american journalists 
the boy and his family planned to rest and sightsee in norways 
capital city before flying to sweden on monday on a trip dubbed 
friendship flight 89 
tony from san juan capistrano calif is carrying letters from 
american schoolchildren to soviet schoolchildren and an 800foot 
friendship scroll signed by 200000 american youngsters he 
plans to present the scroll to president mikhail s gorbachev when 
he reaches moscow 
tony set out june 5 from john wayne airport at costa mesa 
calif on the 19000mile trip dubbed friendship flight 89 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

