a gas explosion in a small coal mine in central 
china killed 18 miners and injured one the official xinhua news 
agency reported sunday 
it said poor ventilation caused the blast thursday in the gutian 
coal mine in xianning city in hubei province 
the mine is owned by the local government but a private 
individual contracted to manage it in january the report said it 
said the dead were local farmers employed by the contractor 
more than 4000 miners died in accidents in china in 1988 the 
worst year for mine disasters in 40 years of communist rule 
most mines in china lack modern equipment and safety provisions 
