<TEXT>
nuclear power stations provided nearly 25 percent of 
all the electricity produced during 1988 in the united states and 23 
other developed freemarket countries according to a report 
during that year the amount of electricity generated by nuclear 
power in those 24 countries rose by 89 percent to 235 percent the 
report said 
it said that figure will peak in 1990 at 238 percent before 
decreasing gradually to 227 percent by 2000 
the 24 countries belong to the organization for economic 
cooperation and development and the report was released saturday by 
its nuclear energy agency 
the report said nuclear power generated 195 percent of the 
electricity in the united states in 1988 far less than the 70 
percent in france 66 percent in belgium 47 percent in sweden 37 
percent in switzerland 36 percent in finland and spain 34 percent 
in west germany and 27 percent in japan 
