the nations mayors moved sunday toward a 
strong new policy statement advocating higher federal taxes with 
republican mayors firmly in support of the departure from 
administration policy 
the proposed resolution before the us conference of mayors at 
its annual meeting called on congress and the bush administration 
to raise revenues in a fair equitable and progressive way 
the mayors from more than 200 cities neared approval on a wide 
range of resolutions on other issues including one on the drug 
problem that calls for a ban on the possession of semiautomatic 
assault weapons it also calls for converting closed and underused 
military bases to use as prisons and drug treatment centers 
the position on gun control would go far beyond the bush 
administrations current ban on the importation of 
foreignmanufactured semiautomatics it would ban the domestic 
manufacture and sale as well as banning possession 
