a light earthquake shook the seattle area sunday 
afternoon but no damage was reported authorities said 
the 138 pm quake shook the puget sound area and was also felt 
in tacoma and olympia and as far north as victoria and sidney on 
vancouver island in canada the us geological survey said 
the temblor which measured 44 on the richter scale and was 30 
miles deep was centered about 10 miles southwest of bremerton 
which is 25 miles west of seattle said steve malone of the 
university of washington geophysics center 
id be surprised if any damage occurred from an earthquake that 
deep malone said there were no reports of damage 
an earthquake measured at 43 on the richter scale occurred in 
the same general area on march 11 1988 said don finley of the 
usgs office in golden colo 
the richter scale is a gauge of the energy released by an 
earthquake as measured by the ground motion recorded on a 
seismograph 
an earthquake of 35 can cause slight damage in the local area 4 
moderate damage 5 considerable damage and 6 severe damage a 7 
reading is a major earthquake capable of widespread heavy 
damage 
